    "explanation": "<p>Since $3^{\\circ}$ alkyl halides prefer to under go elimination rather than substitution, therefore sodium tert-butoxide react with tert-butyl bromide or chlorides to form elimination product isobutylene rather than substitution product di-tert-butyl ether.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m97zpct0/7405b315-eee9-456b-8641-2a0ce2f04725/7731e630-1430-11f0-b5b6-97ae850aee72/file-jaoe38c1m97zpct1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m97zpct0/7405b315-eee9-456b-8641-2a0ce2f04725/7731e630-1430-11f0-b5b6-97ae850aee72/file-jaoe38c1m97zpct1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2024 Chemistry - Alcohol, Phenols and Ethers Question 1 English Explanation\"></p>",
